text.__SUMMARY__: Conus symmetricus is an extinct species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.
text.Description: The size of the shell varies between 17 mm and 46 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species is only known as a fossil from the Neogene of the Dominican Republic.
text.References:
Sowerby I GB. Descriptions of new species of fossil shells found by J. S. Heniker, Esq. Q J Geol Soc London. 1850;6: 44–53.
Hendricks J.R. (2015). Glowing seashells: diversity of fossilized coloration patterns on coral reef-associated cone snail (Gastropoda: Conidae) shells from the Neogene of the Dominican Republic. PLoS ONE. 10(4): e0120924
